from pyclustering.cluster.bsas import bsas, bsas_visualizer

# Prepare algorithm's parameters.
n_theta = 50
thresholdmin = 0.25 * meani
thresholdmax = 1.75 * meani
threshold=(thresholdmax - thresholdmin) / (n_theta - 1)

print(threshold)

max_clusters = 3

# Create instance of BSAS algorithm.
bsas_instance= bsas(X2, max_clusters, threshold)
bsas_instance.process()

# Get clustering results.
clusters = bsas_instance.get_clusters()
representatives = bsas_instance.get_representatives()
# Display results.
bsas_visualizer.show_clusters(X2, clusters, representatives)

from pyclustering.cluster.kmeans import kmeans, kmeans_visualizer
from pyclustering.cluster.center_initializer import kmeans_plusplus_initializer

# Prepare initial centers using K-Means random method.
initial_centers = kmeans_plusplus_initializer(X2, 2).initialize()

# Create instance of K-Means algorithm with prepared centers.
kmeans_instance = kmeans(X2, initial_centers)

# Run cluster analysis and obtain results.
kmeans_instance.process()
clusters = kmeans_instance.get_clusters()
final_centers = kmeans_instance.get_centers()

# Visualize obtained results
kmeans_visualizer.show_clusters(X2, clusters, final_centers)

3. K-Medoids (PAM) Algorithm (Exercise 7.5.2)¶

Repeat Example 7.5.1 for the PAM algorithm

In [9]:
import numpy as np

m1 = np.array([0,0])
m2 = np.array([10,0])
m3 = np.array([0,9])
m4 = np.array([9,8])

S1 = np.array([[1,0], [0, 1]]) 
S2 = np.array([[1,0.2], [0.2, 1.5]]) 
S3 = np.array([[1,0.4], [0.4, 1.1]])
S4 = np.array([[0.3,0.2], [0.2, 0.5]])

N=100
np.random.seed(5)

D1 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m1, S1, N).T
assert D1.shape == (2,100)

D2 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m2, S2, N).T
assert D2.shape == (2,100)

D3 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m3, S3, N).T
assert D3.shape == (2,100)

D4 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m4, S4, N).T
assert D4.shape == (2,100)

Repeat Example 7.5.5 for the PAM algorithm

Using K-Means¶

In [40]:
from pyclustering.cluster.kmeans import kmeans, kmeans_visualizer
from pyclustering.cluster.center_initializer import kmeans_plusplus_initializer
from pyclustering.cluster.elbow import elbow

# create instance of Elbow method using K value from 2 to 10.
kmin, kmax = 2, 10
elbow_instance = elbow(X4, kmin, kmax)

# process input data and obtain results of analysis
elbow_instance.process()
amount_clusters = elbow_instance.get_amount()  # most probable amount of clusters
wce = elbow_instance.get_wce()  # total within-cluster errors for each K

# perform cluster analysis using K-Means algorithm
centers = kmeans_plusplus_initializer(X4, amount_clusters, amount_candidates=kmeans_plusplus_initializer.FARTHEST_CENTER_CANDIDATE).initialize()

kmeans_instance = kmeans(X4, centers)
kmeans_instance.process()

# obtain clustering results and visualize them
clusters = kmeans_instance.get_clusters()
centers = kmeans_instance.get_centers()
kmeans_visualizer.show_clusters(X4, clusters, centers)

from pyclustering.cluster.ema import ema, ema_visualizer, ema_observer

# Create EM observer.
observer = ema_observer()

# Create EM algorithm to allocated four clusters.
